EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO PUBLIC UTILITIES AND CARRIERS -- PUBLIC UTILITIES COMMISSION
***
1 This act would require the public utilities commission to produce a report each January
2 containing an analysis of the electric grid and its ability to supply the electricity needs to power
3 cars, buildings and heat homes within the state. This act would also change the requirement of
4 quarterly meetings of the ratepayers advisory board to monthly meetings. The chairperson of the
5 board would be the commissioner or acting commissioner of the office of energy resources.
6 This act would take effect upon passage.
